The word “score” in the clue is a reference to a musical score. In music, a slur is changing a note without rearticulating. For example, on a bowed instrument, you change notes without re bowing. On a guitar, you change notes without re-plucking a string (some are called “hammer ons” and “pull offs”). You use your fretting hand to change notes without re-picking with your other hand. I suppose a slide or bend on a guitar is a slur as well, as long as you don’t re-pluck in the middle of it. I have no idea how it’s done on a wind instrument. One blow, multi notes?

In musical notation, a slur is indicated by a curved line drawn over the relevant notes.  The clue was trying to misdirect us into thinking about exams graded on a curve.

