@Cal Gal the traditional way it’s done is two boxes.  The one with the person is large enough that the person can pull their knees up and scrunch in the box.  The size of the box is always a little visually misleading in that there is often a black edge which fades into the table so the box looks smaller.  And the person in the box looks bigger with fluffy clothes and the like.

When they scrunch up the fit in the one box easily.

The other box traditionally had a couple of fake feet and shoes.  More modern versions might have moving prop feet.  And the more exotic might even have a hidden 2nd assistant in that box.
